cs.AR, cs.PF, cs.PM, cs.CE, cs.DC

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper focuses on analyzing the architectural features of Intel server processors, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper evaluates the performance of the processors with floating-point workloads and uses microbenchmarks to study the influence of various factors on code performance.
- cs.PM (Performance Metrics): The paper uses performance metrics such as instruction throughput, cache bandwidth and latency, and clock speed to evaluate the processors.
- cs.CE (Computer Engineering): The paper discusses the design and engineering of the processors, including their memory hierarchy and cache snoop modes.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper mentions the impact of Cluster on Die (CoD) on the processors' performance, which is relevant to this sub-category.
